****GIT DAY1******
1. Create a Project
2. Create a GITHUB REPOSITORY
  *go to GitHub
  *Repositories >Create new Repository>first_new_project
3. Create a new Commit for the first time
    *git init
    *git add .
    *git commit -m "first commit"
    *git branch -M main
    *git remote add origin https://github.com/fgkoroglu/first_git_project.git
    *git push -u origin main
    ** refresh

Note: git status --> this is our friend this can be used anytime to see the progress

4. Create a new SECOND COMMIT
    *Create a new java class under first_git_package: MySecondClass
    *Create a new commit and push the code to github
        * git add .
        * git commit -m "added my second java class"
        * git push
5. ADDING SPECIFIC FILES
    *Create 2 JAVA classes : MyThirdClass, MyFourthClass
    *Create a commit with ONLY myFourthClass
        *git add "src/first_git_package/MyFourthClass.java"
        *git commit -m "adding fourth class"
        *git push
6. GIT PULL
    *git pull is used to get the code from github
    *git pull = git fetch + git merge
        NOTE: if git pull trows error then use:
        git fetch
        git merge
    * NOW THAT WE HAVE OUR LOCAL UPDATED, THEN COMMIT THE CODES AND PUSH ALL TOGETHER
        *git add .
        *git commit -m "committing my codes"
        *git push
NOTE: PULL BEFORE PUSH
        *git pull -> git add . -> git commit -m "message" -> git push

        **************************DAY 1. SUMMARY**************************
******Pre-requisities*******
 *Git install
 *GitHub Account
 *Git Authentication (create token, add username and token so your account verification is complete)

                        ***1.First Time Git Push:*******

*git init
* Follow the instruction in put gitHub repository
    git init
    git add
    git commit -m "first commit"
    git branch  -M main
    git remote add origin https://
    git push -u origin main

*NOTE: If you get error, just google the error message...


                       *******2.Second Time Git Push**********
 git add .
 git commit -m "any message"
 git push

                             ***GIT PULL****
 git pull gets latest github code in our local
 git pull = git fetch + git merge


                                   *****CONFLICT*****

 When we try to merge or pull the code that are at the SAME SPOT but HAS DIFFERENT CODES
 How to resolve Conflict?
 -> Manually fix: Remove the illegal characters(error message),
                  create a new commit(add, commit)
                  push

  ----> To Minimize conflict: we can clone the project, add our new code quickly, then commit then push
                              got clone https://github.com/fgkoroglu/first_git_project.git
                              add your new codes
                              git add .
                              git commit -m
                              git push


       ************************************ DAY 2 *************************************************
Branching

* git branch -a --> show me all branch
* git branch feyza
* git checkout feyza --> to switch from main branch to feyza
* git branch --> * to see if you are in the right branch
* open a class and put main method and sout
--> now push this code to gitHub
* git add .
* git commit -m "committing my 6th branch"
* git push --set-upstream origin feyza --> copied from terminal
* Then codes will be in the remote feyza branch
---> now merge the code to master
* Pull Request ---> means the code need to merged to master


             ****One more side branch flow****

*Create a class
*create a new commit and push
git add .
git commit -m "message"
git push
Then new codes will bbe in remote feyza branch
Then gitHub expert or us will do:
Pull Request
Then Code Review
Then Code Merge




